<p>Mark Spitz is a male Olympic swimmer who represented the United States.

	
		 He has won 11 Olympic medals, including
		 9 gold, 1 silver and 1 bronze. This places him 6th all-time among the most decorated Olympic swimmers. The stroke he was most well-known for was butterfly. He competed at his first Olympics in 1968 and his last in 1972.
  

</p>

